  "output": "# Test Coverage Analysis\n\n**Baseline reality:** zero test infra in this repo — no `vitest`/`jest` devDependency, no `*.test.*`/`*.spec.*` files anywhere. Coverage is 0% for every function below. Skeletons use **Vitest + jsdom**, the natural fit since the project already runs on Vite (`vite.config` extends directly, no new build tool).\n\n```\nskipped: full CI coverage-gate setup, snapshot testing, visual regression. add when the animation code breaks in prod more than once — a portfolio site's ROI on that tooling is low until then.\n```\n\n## Prerequisite (not optional — nothing below runs without it)\n\n```ts\n// vitest.config.ts\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config'\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: { environment: 'jsdom', globals: true },\n})\n```\n`npm i -D vitest jsdom @testing-library/react` → skipped picking a coverage reporter/threshold config, add when a CI gate is wanted.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `src/cinematic/lenisStore.ts`\n\n**Untested:** `set`, `scrollTo`, `stop`, `start` — all four, no callers exercised.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `scrollTo`/`stop`/`start` called before any `set()` — must no-op, not throw (relies on `_instance?.`).\n- `scrollTo` accepts `string | number | HTMLElement` — only one variant needs checking since it just forwards, but the forwarding itself (args + options shape) is untested.\n- Re-`set()` with a new instance must fully replace the old one (no stale reference retained).\n- The easing function is inline and un-exported — currently unverifiable in isolation; only testable indirectly through the `scrollTo` call args.\n\n```ts\n// src/cinematic/lenisStore.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { lenisStore } from './lenisStore'\n\nfunction makeFakeLenis() {\n  return { scrollTo: vi.fn(), stop: vi.fn(), start: vi.fn() }\n}\n\ndescribe('lenisStore', () => {\n  beforeEach(() => lenisStore.set(null))\n\n  it('no-ops when called before set()', () => {\n    expect(() => lenisStore.scrollTo(100)).not.toThrow()\n    expect(() => lenisStore.stop()).not.toThrow()\n    expect(() => lenisStore.start()).not.toThrow()\n  })\n\n  it('forwards scrollTo target and duration/easing options', () => {\n    const fake = makeFakeLenis()\n    lenisStore.set(fake as any)\n    lenisStore.scrollTo('#contact')\n    expect(fake.scrollTo).toHaveBeenCalledWith(\n      '#contact',\n      expect.objectContaining({ duration: 1.4, easing: expect.any(Function) }),\n    )\n  })\n\n  it('accepts number and HTMLElement targets', () => {\n    const fake = makeFakeLenis()\n    lenisStore.set(fake as any)\n    lenisStore.scrollTo(500)\n    lenisStore.scrollTo(document.createElement('div'))\n    expect(fake.scrollTo).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2)\n  })\n\n  it('delegates stop/start to the current instance', () => {\n    const fake = makeFakeLenis()\n    lenisStore.set(fake as any)\n    lenisStore.stop()\n    lenisStore.start()\n    expect(fake.stop).toHaveBeenCalledOnce()\n    expect(fake.start).toHaveBeenCalledOnce()\n  })\n\n  it('replacing the instance stops routing calls to the old one', () => {\n    const first = makeFakeLenis()\n    const second = makeFakeLenis()\n    lenisStore.set(first as any)\n    lenisStore.set(second as any)\n    lenisStore.stop()\n    expect(first.stop).not.toHaveBeenCalled()\n    expect(second.stop).toHaveBeenCalledOnce()\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. `src/cinematic/scrollTimelines.ts`\n\n**Untested:** `buildCameraTimeline` — never invoked outside real DOM usage.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- Initial `gsap.set` state (landscape scale 1, haze alpha 0, train alpha 1/scale 1) never asserted.\n- Timeline tween end-values (`landscape` → 1.9, `train` → 6, haze peak 0.28) — a typo/regression in these numbers (the exact \"cinematic feel\" this file is all about) has no safety net.\n- `scrollTrigger.scrub`/`start`/`end` config wired to the right `trigger` element — untested; a copy-paste bug here (wrong trigger) would silently break scroll sync.\n- No null/undefined guard on `refs` members — function assumes all four are live elements. Not a bug (caller's contract via `RefObject`), but worth one test documenting that a `null` element throws immediately rather than failing silently later, since `useEffect` callers could pass it before ref attachment.\n\n```ts\n// src/cinematic/scrollTimelines.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport { buildCameraTimeline, type CameraRefs } from './scrollTimelines'\n\nfunction makeRefs(): CameraRefs {\n  return {\n    spacer: document.createElement('div'),\n    landscape: document.createElement('div'),\n    haze: document.createElement('div'),\n    train: document.createElement('div'),\n  }\n}\n\ndescribe('buildCameraTimeline', () => {\n  it('sets initial layer state before animating', () => {\n    const refs = makeRefs()\n    buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.landscape, 'scale')).toBe(1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'autoAlpha')).toBe(1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.haze, 'autoAlpha')).toBe(0)\n  })\n\n  it('animates background scale up to 1.9 and train scale up to 6 by timeline end', () => {\n    const refs = makeRefs()\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    tl.progress(1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.landscape, 'scale')).toBeCloseTo(1.9)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'scale')).toBeCloseTo(6)\n  })\n\n  it('fades the train to 0 opacity only at the end of the pass-through', () => {\n    const refs = makeRefs()\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    tl.progress(0.5)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'autoAlpha')).toBeGreaterThan(0)\n    tl.progress(1)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(refs.train, 'autoAlpha')).toBeCloseTo(0)\n  })\n\n  it('wires the scrollTrigger to the spacer element with the documented start/end', () => {\n    const refs = makeRefs()\n    const tl = buildCameraTimeline(refs)\n    const st = tl.scrollTrigger!\n    expect(st.trigger).toBe(refs.spacer)\n    expect(st.vars.start).toBe('top top')\n    expect(st.vars.end).toBe('bottom bottom')\n  })\n\n  it('throws immediately if a ref element is null rather than silently no-op-ing', () => {\n    const refs = { ...makeRefs(), train: null as unknown as HTMLElement }\n    expect(() => buildCameraTimeline(refs)).toThrow()\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. `src/cinematic/useLenis.ts`\n\n**Untested:** the whole hook — mount wiring and unmount cleanup.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `lenisStore.set(lenis)` on mount / `lenisStore.set(null)` on unmount — the module coupling between this hook and the store is exactly the kind of thing that silently breaks if either side changes.\n- `gsap.ticker.add(raf)` must be paired with `gsap.ticker.remove(raf)` on unmount — leak here means a dead Lenis instance keeps ticking after unmount (real risk in React 18 StrictMode double-invoke, which mounts→unmounts→mounts every effect once in dev).\n- `lenis.destroy()` called exactly once on unmount, not on every render.\n- `lenis.on('scroll', ScrollTrigger.update)` wiring — never asserted that scroll events actually forward.\n- **Missing integration test:** double mount/unmount (StrictMode simulation) — verify no duplicate `raf` ticker callbacks accumulate and no double-destroy.\n\n```ts\n// src/cinematic/useLenis.test.tsx\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, afterEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport Lenis from 'lenis'\nimport { useLenis } from './useLenis'\nimport { lenisStore } from './lenisStore'\n\nvi.mock('lenis')\n\ndescribe('useLenis', () => {\n  afterEach(() => vi.restoreAllMocks())\n\n  it('publishes the instance to lenisStore on mount and clears it on unmount', () => {\n    const setSpy = vi.spyOn(lenisStore, 'set')\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    expect(setSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith(expect.any(Lenis))\n    unmount()\n    expect(setSpy).toHaveBeenLastCalledWith(null)\n  })\n\n  it('removes its ticker callback and destroys lenis on unmount', () => {\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(gsap.ticker, 'add')\n    const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(gsap.ticker, 'remove')\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    const raf = addSpy.mock.calls[0][0]\n    unmount()\n    expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith(raf)\n  })\n\n  it('survives a StrictMode-style double mount/unmount without leaking tickers', () => {\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(gsap.ticker, 'add')\n    const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(gsap.ticker, 'remove')\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    unmount()\n    const { unmount: unmount2 } = renderHook(() => useLenis())\n    unmount2()\n    expect(addSpy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2)\n    expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalledTimes(2)\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. `src/cinematic/useMouseParallax.ts`\n\n**Untested:** the whole hook. This one has the most branchy logic of the five files and the least coverage-to-risk ratio right now.\n\n**Gaps (in order of how likely they are to actually break):**\n- **Early-return branches never tested:** `!landscape || !train`, `reduceMotion`, `!finePointer` — three separate ways the hook should attach *no* listeners. Currently nothing proves these guards work; a refactor could silently invert one.\n- **Cleanup correctness:** unmount must `removeEventListener` both `pointermove` and `mouseleave`, `killTweensOf` only `x,y,rotationX,rotationY` (not `scale`/`yPercent`, which belong to the scroll timeline — the whole coexistence contract the docblock describes), and reset those four channels to 0.\n- **Clamping edge cases:** `clientX`/`clientY` outside the viewport (can happen with `passive` pointer events near window edges, or synthetic events in tests) — `nx`/`ny` must clamp to `[-1, 1]`, not extrapolate.\n- **`pointerleave`/`mouseleave` reset path** — never verified that leaving the window eases all six channels back to 0 rather than freezing at the last position.\n- **No integration test** proving parallax (`x`/`y`/`rotationX`/`rotationY`) and the scroll timeline (`scale`/`yPercent`) truly write disjoint channels and don't visually fight — this is the load-bearing claim in the docblock and is currently backed by reasoning, not a test.\n\n```ts\n// src/cinematic/useMouseParallax.test.tsx\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport { useMouseParallax } from './useMouseParallax'\n\nfunction refOf(el: HTMLElement | null) {\n  return { current: el }\n}\n\nfunction mockMedia(reduceMotion: boolean, finePointer: boolean) {\n  vi.stubGlobal('matchMedia', (query: string) => ({\n    matches: query.includes('reduce') ? reduceMotion : finePointer,\n    media: query,\n    addEventListener: vi.fn(),\n    removeEventListener: vi.fn(),\n  }))\n}\n\ndescribe('useMouseParallax', () => {\n  beforeEach(() => mockMedia(false, true))\n\n  it('attaches no listeners when either ref is null', () => {\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax(refOf(null), refOf(document.createElement('div'))))\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('skips wiring for prefers-reduced-motion users', () => {\n    mockMedia(true, true)\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax(refOf(document.createElement('div')), refOf(document.createElement('div'))),\n    )\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('skips wiring for coarse (touch) pointers', () => {\n    mockMedia(false, false)\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax(refOf(document.createElement('div')), refOf(document.createElement('div'))),\n    )\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('clamps offsets for pointer coordinates outside the viewport', () => {\n    const landscape = document.createElement('div')\n    const train = document.createElement('div')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax(refOf(landscape), refOf(train)))\n\n    window.dispatchEvent(\n      new MouseEvent('pointermove', { clientX: -5000, clientY: 999999 }) as PointerEvent,\n    )\n    // After clamping, nx/ny saturate at -1/1 — background shift caps at BG_SHIFT_X/Y.\n    expect(Math.abs(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x') as number)).toBeLessThanOrEqual(10)\n    expect(Math.abs(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'y') as number)).toBeLessThanOrEqual(7)\n  })\n\n  it('eases back to zero on mouseleave', () => {\n    const landscape = document.createElement('div')\n    const train = document.createElement('div')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax(refOf(landscape), refOf(train)))\n\n    window.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('pointermove', { clientX: 0, clientY: 0 }) as PointerEvent)\n    document.documentElement.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('mouseleave'))\n    gsap.getTweensOf(landscape).forEach((t) => t.progress(1))\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x')).toBeCloseTo(0)\n  })\n\n  it('removes listeners and resets only x/y/rotationX/rotationY on unmount, leaving scale untouched', () => {\n    const landscape = document.createElement('div')\n    const train = document.createElement('div')\n    gsap.set(landscape, { scale: 1.9 }) // simulate scroll timeline having already set this\n    const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'removeEventListener')\n\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useMouseParallax(refOf(landscape), refOf(train)))\n    unmount()\n\n    expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function))\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x')).toBe(0)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'scale')).toBe(1.9) // untouched — the coexistence contract\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. `src/components/contactRevealEvent.ts`\n\nJust an exported string constant — no logic to unit test in isolation.\n\n**Real gap is integration-level, and it's outside the given file set:** whatever dispatches `CONTACT_REVEALED` (WorkSection's ScrollTrigger `onComplete`) and whatever listens (`ContactSection`, presumably via `window.addEventListener(CONTACT_REVEALED, ...)`) have no test proving the event actually round-trips, or that `ContactSection` really \"never hides again\" after receiving it once (the comment's core invariant).\n\n```ts\n// src/components/contactRevealEvent.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'\nimport { CONTACT_REVEALED } from './contactRevealEvent'\n\ndescribe('contactRevealEvent', () => {\n  it('is a stable, non-empty event name', () => {\n    expect(CONTACT_REVEALED).toBe('contact:revealed')\n  })\n})\n```\n```\nskipped: WorkSection→ContactSection round-trip test (dispatch on scroll completion, \"stays revealed\" invariant) — those files weren't in scope here. Add once WorkSection.tsx / ContactSection.tsx are pulled into the same review; that's where the real bug risk lives, not in this one-line constant.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary table\n\n| File | Functions | Coverage now | Highest-risk gap |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `lenisStore.ts` | 4 | 0% | calls before `set()` don't throw |\n| `scrollTimelines.ts` | 1 | 0% | tween end-values / trigger wiring silently regress |\n| `useLenis.ts` | 1 hook | 0% | ticker leak across StrictMode double-mount |\n| `useMouseParallax.ts` | 1 hook | 0% | guard branches (reduced-motion/touch/null-ref) unverified |\n| `contactRevealEvent.ts` | const | n/a | real gap is the (out-of-scope) dispatch/listen integration |\n\nBiggest lever for the least effort: `useMouseParallax`'s three early-return guards and `useLenis`'s cleanup — both are one-line-of-logic-away from a real regression (motion firing for reduced-motion users, or a ticker leak) and currently have nothing catching it.\n",
