        "title": "4. `src/cinematic/useMouseParallax.ts`",
        "content": "\n**Untested:** the whole hook. This one has the most branchy logic of the five files and the least coverage-to-risk ratio right now.\n\n**Gaps (in order of how likely they are to actually break):**\n- **Early-return branches never tested:** `!landscape || !train`, `reduceMotion`, `!finePointer` — three separate ways the hook should attach *no* listeners. Currently nothing proves these guards work; a refactor could silently invert one.\n- **Cleanup correctness:** unmount must `removeEventListener` both `pointermove` and `mouseleave`, `killTweensOf` only `x,y,rotationX,rotationY` (not `scale`/`yPercent`, which belong to the scroll timeline — the whole coexistence contract the docblock describes), and reset those four channels to 0.\n- **Clamping edge cases:** `clientX`/`clientY` outside the viewport (can happen with `passive` pointer events near window edges, or synthetic events in tests) — `nx`/`ny` must clamp to `[-1, 1]`, not extrapolate.\n- **`pointerleave`/`mouseleave` reset path** — never verified that leaving the window eases all six channels back to 0 rather than freezing at the last position.\n- **No integration test** proving parallax (`x`/`y`/`rotationX`/`rotationY`) and the scroll timeline (`scale`/`yPercent`) truly write disjoint channels and don't visually fight — this is the load-bearing claim in the docblock and is currently backed by reasoning, not a test.\n\n```ts\n// src/cinematic/useMouseParallax.test.tsx\nimport { describe, it, expect, vi, beforeEach } from 'vitest'\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react'\nimport gsap from 'gsap'\nimport { useMouseParallax } from './useMouseParallax'\n\nfunction refOf(el: HTMLElement | null) {\n  return { current: el }\n}\n\nfunction mockMedia(reduceMotion: boolean, finePointer: boolean) {\n  vi.stubGlobal('matchMedia', (query: string) => ({\n    matches: query.includes('reduce') ? reduceMotion : finePointer,\n    media: query,\n    addEventListener: vi.fn(),\n    removeEventListener: vi.fn(),\n  }))\n}\n\ndescribe('useMouseParallax', () => {\n  beforeEach(() => mockMedia(false, true))\n\n  it('attaches no listeners when either ref is null', () => {\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax(refOf(null), refOf(document.createElement('div'))))\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('skips wiring for prefers-reduced-motion users', () => {\n    mockMedia(true, true)\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax(refOf(document.createElement('div')), refOf(document.createElement('div'))),\n    )\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('skips wiring for coarse (touch) pointers', () => {\n    mockMedia(false, false)\n    const addSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'addEventListener')\n    renderHook(() =>\n      useMouseParallax(refOf(document.createElement('div')), refOf(document.createElement('div'))),\n    )\n    expect(addSpy).not.toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function), expect.anything())\n  })\n\n  it('clamps offsets for pointer coordinates outside the viewport', () => {\n    const landscape = document.createElement('div')\n    const train = document.createElement('div')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax(refOf(landscape), refOf(train)))\n\n    window.dispatchEvent(\n      new MouseEvent('pointermove', { clientX: -5000, clientY: 999999 }) as PointerEvent,\n    )\n    // After clamping, nx/ny saturate at -1/1 — background shift caps at BG_SHIFT_X/Y.\n    expect(Math.abs(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x') as number)).toBeLessThanOrEqual(10)\n    expect(Math.abs(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'y') as number)).toBeLessThanOrEqual(7)\n  })\n\n  it('eases back to zero on mouseleave', () => {\n    const landscape = document.createElement('div')\n    const train = document.createElement('div')\n    renderHook(() => useMouseParallax(refOf(landscape), refOf(train)))\n\n    window.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('pointermove', { clientX: 0, clientY: 0 }) as PointerEvent)\n    document.documentElement.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('mouseleave'))\n    gsap.getTweensOf(landscape).forEach((t) => t.progress(1))\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x')).toBeCloseTo(0)\n  })\n\n  it('removes listeners and resets only x/y/rotationX/rotationY on unmount, leaving scale untouched', () => {\n    const landscape = document.createElement('div')\n    const train = document.createElement('div')\n    gsap.set(landscape, { scale: 1.9 }) // simulate scroll timeline having already set this\n    const removeSpy = vi.spyOn(window, 'removeEventListener')\n\n    const { unmount } = renderHook(() => useMouseParallax(refOf(landscape), refOf(train)))\n    unmount()\n\n    expect(removeSpy).toHaveBeenCalledWith('pointermove', expect.any(Function))\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'x')).toBe(0)\n    expect(gsap.getProperty(landscape, 'scale')).toBe(1.9) // untouched — the coexistence contract\n  })\n})\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 2
      },
      {
        "title": "5. `src/components/contactRevealEvent.ts`",
        "content": "\nJust an exported string constant — no logic to unit test in isolation.\n\n**Real gap is integration-level, and it's outside the given file set:** whatever dispatches `CONTACT_REVEALED` (WorkSection's ScrollTrigger `onComplete`) and whatever listens (`ContactSection`, presumably via `window.addEventListener(CONTACT_REVEALED, ...)`) have no test proving the event actually round-trips, or that `ContactSection` really \"never hides again\" after receiving it once (the comment's core invariant).\n\n```ts\n// src/components/contactRevealEvent.test.ts\nimport { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest'\nimport { CONTACT_REVEALED } from './contactRevealEvent'\n\ndescribe('contactRevealEvent', () => {\n  it('is a stable, non-empty event name', () => {\n    expect(CONTACT_REVEALED).toBe('contact:revealed')\n  })\n})\n```\n```\nskipped: WorkSection→ContactSection round-trip test (dispatch on scroll completion, \"stays revealed\" invariant) — those files weren't in scope here. Add once WorkSection.tsx / ContactSection.tsx are pulled into the same review; that's where the real bug risk lives, not in this one-line constant.\n```\n\n---\n\n",
        "level": 2
      },
      {
        "title": "Summary table",
        "content": "| File | Functions | Coverage now | Highest-risk gap |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `lenisStore.ts` | 4 | 0% | calls before `set()` don't throw |\n| `scrollTimelines.ts` | 1 | 0% | tween end-values / trigger wiring silently regress |\n| `useLenis.ts` | 1 hook | 0% | ticker leak across StrictMode double-mount |\n| `useMouseParallax.ts` | 1 hook | 0% | guard branches (reduced-motion/touch/null-ref) unverified |\n| `contactRevealEvent.ts` | const | n/a | real gap is the (out-of-scope) dispatch/listen integration |\n\nBiggest lever for the least effort: `useMouseParallax`'s three early-return guards and `useLenis`'s cleanup — both are one-line-of-logic-away from a real regression (motion firing for reduced-motion users, or a ticker leak) and currently have nothing catching it.",
